You can run tests by using `cargo xtask test`.
Each layer of the application should use integration tests.
There is builtin test runner that you can use like this:


#[test]
fn integration() -> test_runner::Result {
    test_runner::test_snapshots("docs/", "<extension>", |input, _deps| {
        function that takes input: &str and returns String
    })
}

It runs markdown files like `docs/001.md` and finds every codeblock with the same <extension> as requested.

ALWAYS make sure that tests are passing with `cargo xtask test`
ALWAYS use `cargo xtask clippy` and `cargo xtask fmt` after making the code passing tests.